RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 2 4F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 7700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 19, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BLUE CHIP BETTY Broke on top, cleared field and led on rail, ran in line of three around turn, confidently through lane. MY FUNNY GAL Moved between from break, pressed leader opening stages, challenged at eighth pole two wide, shrugged off by winner. LOW DOSE Set up second flight outside, circled four wide on bend, willingly late. SASSY EDIE Took hard contact early stages from #1 MOUNTAIN PASS, recovered to track along the rail, belatedly gained inside while passing tiring foes. TRIPDOWNMEMORYLANE Was in touch three wide backstretch, three wide around turn, asked at quarter pole for run, faded lane. MOUNTAIN PASS Shifted out at the break, sharply took off towards outer rail, first squeezed #2 WISHFUL WON out of spot, then initiated hard contact with #3 SASSY EDIE, once clear of any other rivals that could be affected was hard to handle and ended up close to outer rail, re-engaged heading into lane, minor headway late. WISHFUL WON Shuffled out sharply between horses shortly after the start, lagged from that point, did not impact. AN OBJECTION FROM THE RIDER OF #2 WISHFUL WON WAS LODGED AGAINST #1 MOUNTAIN PASS AND #3 SASSY EDIE REGARDING A BACKSTRETCH INCIDENT. AFTER REVIEW, STEWARDS DETERMINED #1 MOUNTAIN PASS IMPACTED THE PLACING OF #2 WISHFUL WON. #1 MOUNTAIN PASS WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM SIXTH TO SEVENTH.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Mountain Pass
ENTRY.COMMENT: Shifted out brk, compromised rivals, took off to outer rail

ENTRY.NAME: Wishful Won
ENTRY.COMMENT: Shuffled out sharply between, lagged, no impact

ENTRY.NAME: Sassy Edie
ENTRY.COMMENT: Contact ins, tracked rail, belatedly on inside

ENTRY.NAME: Low Dose

ENTRY.COMMENT: 2nd flight outside, circled 4w bend, willingly late

ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke best, cleared to rail, line of three, confidently

ENTRY.NAME: My Funny Gal

ENTRY.COMMENT: Moved between, pressed, challenge 1/8 2w, shrugged off

ENTRY.NAME: Tripdownmemorylane
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w backstretch, 3w turn, asked 1/4, faded lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 3 4F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 8100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE FEBRUARY 19. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKY JACK Pressed two wide in the opening stages, moved up to engage leader at quarter pole, battled with rival down the lane, grinded past, outlasted rival in closing stages. BAPTISM Broke sharply, cleared over to rail, led until being joined by rival at quarter pole, ding donged down the lane inside of rival, outfinished late. A GEM IS A GEM Outrun early, made a three wide bid while gaining, surged to pass tiring for minor awards. AFTER THE CANDY Sat in pocket off of top two rivals, called upon at quarter pole, swung to three path for the lane but shifted back to rail a handful of yards later, no match. STONUS MAXIMUS Stalked in three path, made two wide bid in second flight past quarter pole while idling, faded down the lane.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Outrun early, 3w gain outs, passed tiring while gaining

ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalked 3p, 2w bid while idling, faded

ENTRY.NAME: Rocky Jack
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pressed 2w, engaged 1/4, battled, grinded, outlasted rival

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COASTAL RUN Sent hard from the blocks and maintained inside path to first turn, dueled throughout at an honest pace before shaking off sticky rival at the eighth pole, won battle, drew off convincingly. MADISON'S QUARTERS Tracked well off a hot pace on the rail, advanced at the quarter pole while remaining inside, passed tiring rival late for place honors. MISS AGGIE BLING Dueled at a dogged pace outside of rival, was unable to keep pace when the running got real, faded down the lane. ORATORY GLORY Set up well off the speed in the three path, asked at quarter pole, never menaced. IZANAMI Taken back early, called upon heading into bend, never fired.

MORE HONOR Stalked inside tucked behind leading trio, swung out to the six path for the stretch run where he boldly gained while hanging on the wrong lead, continued momentum to wire but ran out of time. KING LEBRON Hustled out of gate, vied along rail with rival outside, passed by gaining foe at three-eighths pole, asked after being overtaken, gave way. ROYAL TAP Vied between horses for lead, passed by gaining runner at three-eighths pole, asked at three-sixteenths pole for run, idled in run home. RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 7800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 19, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINEHUNTER Made the lead with ease, remained unchallenged while responding to rider's every cue, called upon at the eighth pole to stay in command, coasted home. GONE SOMEWHERE Stalked between rivals just off the leader, asked at quarter pole to proceed, two wide bid around the far turn, no match for lone leader. FULL DRAW Brushed inside from the break, made move to the rail in approach to the first turn, sat in pocket behind leader and inside of two stalking rivals, made move at three-sixteenths pole, outfinished while moving to wire on the wrong lead. FINAL ROSE Tracked well off the pace throughout, commenced a move beginning in the five path around the far turn, showed mild late gain to the wire. HULA KING Stalked three wide in first turn run, maintained position until far turn, outpaced when three fellow top flight runners made moves, could not advance down the lane. OUTLAW BY NATURE Missed the break, lagged far behind and was far from in touch with the field, passed one tiring rival down the lane. AUTISM SAVANT Settled off the pace inside of rivals, in the run to the first turn shifted well out to the five path for clear air, failed to improve from that point, faded from the quarter pole to the wire.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Off pace inside, shifted to 5p 1st, faded 1/4
